[modifier]

Target output is a React component written in TypeScript.

[modifier]

The component receives all data and event handlers through props. It does not store todos internally and does not perform persistence.

[modifier]

Use plain semantic HTML elements and CSS class names only. Do not use inline styles, CSS-in-JS, component libraries, icon libraries, animation libraries, or utility CSS frameworks.

[type Todo]

A todo item with an id string, title string, completion status boolean, and creation date string in ISO 8601 format.

[type Todo Filter]

A filter value that is one of: all, active, completed.

[type Todo List CSS Classes]

Use "todo-list" for the container.
Use "todo-row" for each todo row.
Use "completed" for completed todo rows.
Use "selected" for the selected filter button.

[function Filter Todos]

Given an array of Todo values and a Todo Filter, return the todos matching the filter.
The all filter returns every todo.
The active filter returns todos whose completion status is false.
The completed filter returns todos whose completion status is true.

[function Sort Todos]

Given an array of Todo values, return a new array sorted by creation date descending.
Do not mutate the original array.

[type Todo List Props]

The props for Todo List Component.

It includes:
- todos: an array of Todo values
- selected filter: the currently selected Todo Filter
- on filter change: a handler that receives the newly selected Todo Filter and returns nothing
- on todo completion toggle: a handler that receives the todo id and the new completion status, and returns nothing

[function Todo List Component]

Render a React component using Todo List Props.

First Sort Todos, then Filter Todos.

Render a heading with text "Todos".

Render one filter button for each Todo Filter value.

The selected filter button is the one whose Todo Filter value equals the selected filter prop.

The selected filter button uses the selected CSS class.

When a filter button is clicked, call on filter change with that button's Todo Filter value.

Render one row per visible todo.

Each row shows a checkbox bound to the todo completion status and a text label containing the todo title.

Use Todo List CSS Classes for styling hooks.

When a checkbox changes, call the completion toggle handler with the todo id and the new completion status.

If no todos are visible, display "No todos to show."